label("$B$",B,NE);
label("$C$",C,SE);
label("$D$",D,SW);
label("$E$",Ep,W);
label("$F$",F,E);
label("$G$",G,N);
label("$x$",midpoint(G--B),W);
label("$3y$",midpoint(B--F),W);
label("$4y$",midpoint(F--C),W);
label("$7$",midpoint(A--B),N);
label("$10$",midpoint(C--D),N); [/asy]

Let $E$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $B$ to $\overline{CD}$. Then $AB = DE$ and $BE =
AD = 7$. By the Pythagorean Theorem, \begin{align*}
AD^2 = BE^2 &= BC^2 - CE^2\\
&= (CD+AB)^2 - (CD - AB)^2\\
&=(CD+AB+CD-AB)(CD+AB-CD+AB)\\
&=4\cdot CD \cdot AB.
\end{align*}Hence, $AB \cdot CD = AD^2/4=7^2/4=49/4=\boxed{12.25}$.

